# TypeScript Code Style

- `strict` mode on; no implicit `any`; prefer `unknown` over `any`.
- Prefer `type`/`interface` over loose objects; readonly where possible.
- Pure functions and small modules; explicit return types on public APIs.
- ESLint + Prettier; build clean (no TS errors, no lint errors).
- Async/await over raw promises; handle rejections.
- Comments in English; explain intent, not mechanics.

## Testing

- Vitest/Jest; unit tests for logic, integration tests for I/O boundaries.
- Cover happy path, edge cases, and error paths from acceptance criteria.
